## CHAPTER 4. THE COMPLETE 25-PROMPT TRAINING SYSTEM

The 25-moment training journey is the foundation of the product.
It must feel warm, guided, ceremonial, and deeply human.

Everything here is now fully aligned with:

voice record

voice continuity

artifact framing

keepsake framing

stewardship

emotional arc

model needs

prototype v7

### 4.1 Purpose of the 25 Moments

The voice record is created by collecting three core types of vocal data:

**A. Natural tone**
The everyday speaking voice. Unforced, conversational, relaxed.

**B. Emotional range**
Warmth, stories, memories, encouragement.
This adds depth, variation, and humanity.

**C. Speech identity**
Name, number sequences, addresses, counting.
This adds rhythm, inflection, clarity, personality.

The 25 prompts are designed to:

increase the quality of the voice model

create variety in sound, pacing, emotional tone

give users a guided, meaningful experience

build a sense of ceremony and continuity

make the journey feel like shaping a keepsake

Completing all 25 is required to generate the preserved voice.

### 4.2 Structure of the Training Journey

Your 25 prompts fall into three stages.
Each stage has a distinct emotional feel and purpose.

**Stage 1: Quick Start**

5 prompts
3 to 4 minutes
Focus: everyday tone
Emotional feel: light, grounded, non-intimidating

**Stage 2: Emotional Range**

12 prompts
5 to 6 minutes
Focus: warm stories, memories, encouragement
Emotional feel: depth, intimacy, reflection

**Stage 3: Personality and Rhythm**

8 prompts
3 to 4 minutes
Focus: identity statements, cadence, unique sound
Emotional feel: warm, personal, signature

Total time: 11 to 14 minutes
Total prompts: 25
Required for full continuity.

### 4.3 Stage-by-Stage UX Principles

**Stage 1 UX Goals**

Build confidence early

Zero emotional risk

Simple topics

Short prompts

Soothing tone

Soft progress guidance

Light celebration

This stage is where the user settles into their own voice.

Stone state: recording with low amplitude
Copy tone: gentle, warm, conversational

**Stage 2 UX Goals**

Invite warmth and reflection

Gently deepen emotional expression

Allow pauses and silence as needed

Normalize vulnerability

Encourage natural storytelling

Integrate voice continuity language

Stone state: richer glow, wider breath
Copy tone: supportive, validating, steady

**Stage 3 UX Goals**

Bring personality into the record

Strengthen clarity

Capture identity markers

Prepare for playback

Signal that the voice record is almost complete

Stone state: stable, rhythmic
Copy tone: steady, warm, grateful

### 4.4 Full Prompt List With Correct Staging

Below is your exact script, cleaned and organized to production standards but without altering your voice.

**STAGE 1: QUICK START**

5 prompts
3 to 4 minutes

**Prompt 1**

Good morning. My name is {userName}, and I am here in {city}.
It is a beautiful moment to begin this.
I feel relaxed and ready to hear how my voice will sound.

Variations: afternoon, evening, late night.

**Prompt 2**

You know what always makes me smile? A really good cup of coffee in the morning.
There is something about that first sip when it is hot and fresh.
It makes everything feel right.
It is the little things that make your day feel better.

**Prompt 3**

This week has been pretty good.
I got out for a walk around {city}, and it felt nice.
The weather was decent, and the fresh air cleared my head.
Sometimes the quiet, simple days are exactly what we need.

**Prompt 4**

There is a spot in {city} that I really love.
It is nothing fancy, just a quiet place where I can sit and think.
When I am there, everything feels peaceful.
Everyone needs a place like that to breathe and feel like themselves.

**Prompt 5**

If you are listening to this, I want you to know something.
Whatever you are going through, you are doing better than you think.
Life can be hard, but you are here and still showing up.
Give yourself some credit. You have earned it.

**STAGE 2: EMOTIONAL RANGE**

12 prompts
5 to 6 minutes

**Prompt 6**

I remember when I was a kid.
Summer days felt endless and full of laughter.
We did not have much, but we had each other.
Those simple moments still stay with me.

Variation: era specific.

**Prompt 7**

There is someone in my life who has always been there for me.
Through everything.
They taught me what real loyalty looks like.
I would not be who I am without them.

**Prompt 8**

What would I tell my younger self?
Stop worrying so much about what people think.
Do the things that make you happy.
It really does all work out in the end.

Variation: era specific.

**Prompt 9**

I remember doing something that scared me for years.
My heart was pounding, but I did it anyway.
That moment taught me that I am stronger than I realized.

**Prompt 10**

My perfect day is simple.
Wake up without an alarm.
A good cup of coffee.
A walk around {city}.
Dinner with people I love.
Good food, good company, good conversation.
That is all I need.

**Prompt 11**

I am grateful for the people who have stayed in my life.
The ones who showed up during the hard times and the good ones.
That kind of presence matters more than anything.

**Prompt 12**

Life taught me that I cannot control everything.
I used to try.
But letting go is sometimes the only way forward.
It is scary, but it is freeing.

**Prompt 13**

I remember being terrified before doing something new.
My hands were shaking.
My mind raced.
But I did it, and it turned out okay.
It taught me something important about courage.

**Prompt 14**

If you are having a rough day, I want you to know something.
You do not have to be strong all the time.
Tomorrow is a new start.
You are stronger than you think.

**Prompt 15**

Here is what I have learned.
What really matters is not the big stuff.
It is the shared moments and the people who make life feel meaningful.

**Prompt 16**

I want you to know I believe in you.
You might be doubting yourself right now.
But I know what you are capable of.
Keep going. You can do this.

**Prompt 17**

Here is what I learned about love.
It is not grand gestures.
It is showing up.
It is the quiet, everyday moments.
That is where the real magic lives.

**STAGE 3: FINAL TOUCH**

8 prompts
3 to 4 minutes

**Prompt 18**

I want you to know you are special to me.
Whatever happens, remember that you matter.
You are loved, and I am here for you.

Relationship variants included.

**Prompt 19**

I hope we all slow down a little.
Take time to enjoy the small things.
Spend more time with the people we love.
Life is short.
I hope we all remember to live.

**Prompt 20**

When I think about home, it is not really a place.
Home is the people you love.
It is where you can be yourself.
I feel lucky to have that.

**Prompt 21**

Here is something I wish someone told me.
Be kind to others, yes.
But be kind to yourself too.
We are all doing the best we can.

**Prompt 22**

Let us count together.
One to ten.
Then ten back to one.
This helps capture rhythm and clarity.

**Prompt 23**

Here is my information.
You can reach me at five-five-five, two-one-two, three-four-five-six.
My address is four twenty seven Oak Street, apartment two B, {city}.
Today's date is {date}, around {time}.

**Prompt 24**

You know what always makes me laugh?
When you trip over nothing and look around to see if anyone saw.
We all do it.
It is silly, but it is human.

**Prompt 25**

Alright, that is a wrap.
Thank you for being here for this.
I hope this brings you joy whenever you hear it.
You are loved, valued, and doing better than you think.
Take care of yourself.
Bye for now.

Relationship variant included.

### 4.5 Dynamic Personalization Logic

The following metadata fills into specific prompts:

{userName}

{city}

{date}

{time}

era variants (1950s to 2000s)

relationship variants

time of day

This yields dozens of natural variations without extra engineering overhead.

### 4.6 Progress Logic

The UI must reflect accurate progress counting:

Stage 1: 5 moments

Stage 2: 12 moments

Stage 3: 8 moments

Total: 25

Progress ring should animate subtly between prompts.
Stone should pulse warmly after each moment.

### 4.7 Emotional Pacing Requirements

The flow must:

start lightly

deepen slowly

include grounding moments

rise into warmth

resolve gently

end with gratitude and closure

This pacing is key for emotional safety and model performance.

