## CHAPTER 5. SOFT PRESERVATION OFFER V3

(after all 25 moments and after voice processing completes)

The preservation offer is not a paywall.
It is an invitation to safeguard something meaningful.

ESSENCE must present this moment with warmth, respect, and ceremony.

This is the most sensitive copy in the entire product because it comes after the user has invested deeply and right before the emotional reveal of hearing their preserved voice.

The experience must feel like stewardship.
Not monetization.

### 5.1 Placement Logic

This offer appears directly after:

All 25 moments are captured

The system completes model training

The Breath Stone settles into a reverent glow

A short pause screen prepares the user emotionally

Then the offer screen fades in gently.

This comes before the first playback moment.

### 5.2 Purpose and Philosophy

The offer explains:

what the user has created

why it is valuable

what ESSENCE can safeguard

what is free

what protection means

what upgrading unlocks

ESSENCE must avoid fear-based language.
This is about care, not urgency.

### 5.3 Emotional Intent

The tone here should feel like:

a gentle guide

a respectful steward

a warm presence

a curator of something precious

This is not sales language.
This is caretaking language.

### 5.4 Screen Layout

**Breath Stone**
Celebrate state.
Soft warm glow.
A sense of depth.

**Top Label**
YOUR PRESERVED VOICE IS READY

**Title**
Your voice has reached full depth.

**Body**
You have shaped twenty five moments.
Your preserved voice is now steady, natural, and unmistakably yours.
It is a complete voice record, ready to be used for future messages.

**Sub body**
Here is how we can help you care for it.

**Two Cards (stacked)**

**Card A: Free Tier**

**Title**
Keep your voice as a keepsake

**Body**
Your complete voice record stays saved here.
You can create one message to hear how your voice feels when it speaks for you.

**Benefits list**
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Your voice record is stored safely
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ One message included
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ No commitment
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ You can upgrade at any time

**CTA inside card**
Create my first message

This simply moves to the first playback sequence.

**Card B: Activated Protection Tier**

**Title**
Activate long term protection

**Body**
We will maintain your voice so it stays clear and steady for years to come.
Protection lets you create unlimited messages for the people you love.

**Benefits list**
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Long term voice continuity
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Unlimited messages
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Future feature access
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Support whenever you need it

**Price**
4.99 per month

**CTA**
Activate now

### 5.5 Secondary Copy (beneath cards)

Most people choose protection after hearing their voice in action.
There is no pressure.
Your voice stays safe either way.

### 5.6 Button Structure

**Primary CTA (bottom of the screen)**
Continue

This takes the user to their first playback moment.

**Secondary CTA (optional, top right)**
Maybe later

This also takes the user to playback.
The offer returns after first message creation.

### 5.7 Behavioral Logic

**If user chooses "Activate now"**

move into payment screen

after payment, skip free tier flow

go straight to ceremonial playback

Home B loads the paid version

**If user chooses "Create my first message"**

skip payment

proceed to ceremonial playback

Home B loads free tier state

after 1 free message is sent, soft upsell appears later

**If user declines everything**

proceed to playback

soft upsell returns later

### 5.8 Emotional Notes

The offer must always feel like:

"You created something meaningful.
Here is a gentle way to protect it."

Never:

"You must pay to continue."

The user has earned this moment through emotional investment.
They must never feel pushed or restricted.

This is why the first message is free.
It allows them to feel the magic before deciding on protection.

### 5.9 Stone Behavior

soft reverent glow

slow calming pulse

warm edges

depth lighting

subtle shimmer

The stone communicates:

"Your voice is ready.
Take your time."

### 5.10 Error Handling

**If payment fails**
"Something did not go through.
Your voice is safe.
Try again when you are ready."

**If user closes the screen**
They return to the playback moment.

**If internet disconnects**
"Your voice record is saved.
We will continue once you are reconnected."

### 5.11 Summary

The Soft Preservation Offer V3 must feel like:

a warm invitation

the stewardship of a keepsake

the continuation of something sacred

the natural next step in caring for your voice

This is the correct emotional and functional placement.
It is now fully aligned with your brand, your demographic, your prototype, and your long term product strategy.

