## CHAPTER 11. SOFT PRESERVATION OFFER V3

A warm invitation to protect the voice record long term

The preservation offer appears only after the user has:

completed all twenty five prompts

reached the "All moments captured" milestone

waited through model training

heard their preserved voice during the first playback ceremony

This timing is intentional.
The user must feel proud, emotionally moved, and connected before being invited to protect their voice record.

This is not a paywall.
This is stewardship.

### 11.1 Purpose of the Preservation Offer

The soft offer must:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ frame the voice as a keepsake
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ reinforce that the voice record is valuable
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ introduce long term protection
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ avoid pressure or urgency
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ invite the user to protect something meaningful
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ still allow them to continue exploring without committing

The key principle is choice without fear.

### 11.2 Emotional Intent

The tone should feel like:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a curator speaking
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a gentle archivist
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a guide helping them protect something important

No sales energy.
Only stewardship and continuity.

### 11.3 When the Offer Appears

The offer appears immediately after:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ First Playback Moment V2 has completed
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ the user has pressed Continue after hearing their preserved voice

They must hear themselves before being asked.

### 11.4 Screen Layout and Behavior

**Label**

YOUR PRESERVED VOICE

**Title**

Keep your voice protected for the long term.

**Body Copy**

Your voice record is now complete.
You shaped twenty five moments.
Your voice has been preserved with clarity and warmth.

If you would like, we can keep your voice protected so it stays steady and accessible in the years ahead.

Most people choose to activate protection once they hear how natural their voice sounds.

**Value Framing Elements**

Under the body copy, a short list appears with soft icons:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Long term protection for your preserved voice
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Secure storage of all twenty five moments
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Priority care and rebalancing if your voice changes over time
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Access to all message creation features
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Three voice messages included instantly

These must feel like features of preservation, not a subscription list.

**Breath Stone State**

Infused
Warm steady glow
A moment of gentle presence

**Primary CTA**

Activate protection
(subtle price tag appears beneath: 4.99 per month)

**Secondary CTA**

Not now

Secondary CTA continues the flow without penalty.

### 11.5 Handling the Secondary CTA

If the user chooses Not now:

**Transition Screen**

Label: YOUR VOICE IS READY
Title: You can create messages anytime.
Body: Your three included voice messages are waiting.
CTA: Create my first message

**Important**
The voice record always remains preserved for basic access even if protection is not activated.

You are never withholding their keepsake.

### 11.6 Micro Reinforcement After Accepting

If the user activates preservation:

**Label**

VOICE PROTECTION ACTIVATED

**Title**

Your voice is now protected.

**Body**

Your preserved voice will remain secure, steady, and ready to use whenever you need it.
Your three included messages are waiting.

**CTA**

Create my first message

A small confirmation icon and soft animation appears.
The stone brightens slightly for two seconds.

### 11.7 Behavioral Logic

**If user selects "Activate protection"**

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ update their account
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ unlock long term protection flag
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ allow unlimited messages
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ route to message creation flow

**If user selects "Not now"**

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ allow access to three included messages
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ present a soft reminder card inside Home B
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ no hard blocks or restrictions

The offer should never feel like a barrier.

### 11.8 Preservation Offer Card in Home B

A light card appears at the bottom of Home B if the user has not activated protection.

**Card Copy**

Keep your voice protected
Your voice will stay steady and accessible with long term protection.

**CTA:** Activate protection

This card should feel like a quiet invitation, not an advertisement.

### 11.9 Copy and Tone Requirements

The offer uses:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ keepsake language
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ stewardship language
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ long term continuity framing
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ gentle emotional pacing
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ no pressure
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ no technical jargon

Avoid words like:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ subscription
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ billing
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ plan
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ upgrade

Preferred terminology:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ protection
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ keep it safe
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ long term care
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ voice continuity
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ preserved voice
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ voice record
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ keepsake

### 11.10 Developer Requirements

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Offer must only unlock after Model Training and First Playback
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Do not allow message creation if the user has not heard playback yet
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ If user reopens the app after playback but before choosing, the offer must be shown again
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ If user selects Not now, system must unlock one message
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ If user activates protection, set long term protection flag
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Home B must show correct state based on protection flag

### 11.11 Summary

Soft Preservation Offer V3:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ is not a paywall
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ is not urgent
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ is not transactional

It is an invitation to protect a personal keepsake.
It is a moment of pride and care after a deeply emotional process.
It creates a natural bridge between the ceremonial journey and continued creation.

This chapter is now ready to merge into your Master Specification V4.3.

