## CHAPTER 12. FIRST PLAYBACK V2

The ceremonial reveal of the preserved voice

First Playback is the most emotionally charged moment in ESSENCE.
It is the moment where the user hears their preserved voice for the first time after shaping all twenty five moments.
It must feel personal, cinematic, warm, and reverent.

This is the payoff for the entire journey.
It is the proof that their work created something real.

### 12.1 Purpose of First Playback

First Playback should:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ validate the twenty five moment journey
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ make the user feel proud
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ make the voice feel like an artifact
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ deepen trust in ESSENCE
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ create a cinematic reveal experience
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ prepare the user for the preservation offer
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ open the doorway into message creation

This is not a technical demo.
This is a keepsake unveiling.

### 12.2 When the Playback Occurs

The playback screen appears only after:

all twenty five prompts have been fully recorded

the "All moments captured" screen

the full model training sequence

the user taps Continue on the preservation offer screen

Then the stage is set for a controlled emotional moment.

### 12.3 Emotional Intent

The experience must feel like:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ listening to something sacred
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ hearing a version of yourself that you want to protect
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a peaceful reveal
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a moment that makes them pause and reflect

Tone is quiet, warm, respectful, gentle.

### 12.4 First Playback Screen Layout

**Label**

THIS IS YOUR VOICE

**Title**

Your preserved voice is ready.

**Body Copy**

Here is a first message created from the twenty five moments you shared.
It carries the natural sound, tone, and warmth of your preserved voice.

**Playback Card**

This contains:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a title: "Your preserved voice"
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a short generated message (twelve to fifteen seconds)
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a play button
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a visual waveform that responds during playback

**Generated Message Example**

"Hello. This is my voice, preserved from today. I hope it brings comfort and warmth whenever you hear it. Thank you for shaping these moments with me."

This example is for design guidance.
The actual message will be auto generated.

**Breath Stone State**

Playback
Soft inhale and exhale synced to the voice
Warm light that brightens on vowels and softens on pauses
Size: 130 percent
Glow: gentle and continuous

**Primary CTA**

Continue

No secondary CTA is needed here.
The moment must remain emotionally focused and simple.

### 12.5 Playback Behavior

**Before playback**

The card shows a ready state.
No movement except the stone.

**During playback**

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ The waveform animates with peaks and valleys
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ The stone breathes in sync with the message
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ The play button becomes a pause button

**After playback**

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ The stone returns to a steady glow
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Play resets
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ CTA remains visible

The user can replay as many times as they want.

### 12.6 Accessibility Considerations

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Screen reader readable transcript
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Optional captions under the waveform
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Subtle vibration on play for mobile
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ No auto play
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Button sizes optimized for older users

### 12.7 Transition Out of Playback

When the user presses Continue, they are guided into the next ceremony.

**Transition Screen**

Label: YOUR VOICE IS READY
Title: You can now create messages.
Body: Your preserved voice can speak on your behalf anytime you wish.
CTA: Create my first message

This prevents abruptness and maintains the emotional rhythm.

### 12.8 Playback Failure Handling

If the playback cannot generate the message:

**Fallback Copy**

"We could not create your first playback. Your twenty five moments are still preserved. We will regenerate your playback now."

User sees a brief loader and then the playback appears.

No blame or technical language is used.

### 12.9 Developer Requirements

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Requires twenty five complete moments
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Requires trained model
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Playback must stream or play locally without lag
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Must support repeat playback
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Stone must sync with audio waveform
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Must trigger event tracking: FirstPlaybackStarted and FirstPlaybackCompleted

### 12.10 Why This Works

This version of the playback flow:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ creates a moment of reverence
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ reinforces the artifact framing
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ makes the voice feel worth protecting
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ sets up long term protection naturally
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ sets a trustworthy emotional tone
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ leads organically into message creation

It is the emotional center of ESSENCE.

### 12.11 Summary

First Playback V2 is:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a ceremony
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a reveal
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a keepsake moment
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a gentle preparation for message creation
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ a closing chapter to the archival journey
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ an opening chapter to using the preserved voice

