## CHAPTER 15. MESSAGE ARCHIVE AND CONTINUITY HUB

A warm home for saved messages and voice continuity

The Message Archive and Continuity Hub is the emotional library of ESSENCE.
It is not a traditional inbox and not a file system.
It is a gentle collection of moments the user created with their preserved voice.

It must feel like a keepsake drawer or a memory box.
It must encourage calm reflection, not overwhelm.

This is the second major area of the product after Home B.

### 15.1 Purpose of the Archive

The archive exists to:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ store all saved messages created using the preserved voice
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ create a peaceful space where messages can be replayed
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ allow users to revisit memories and sentiments
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ reinforce the value of long term preservation
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ serve as the place where continuity and ongoing care features live
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ support growth into future continuity features

The archive must feel emotional, safe, and warm.

### 15.2 When the Archive Becomes Available

The Message Archive is accessible only after:

all twenty five prompts are complete

the preserved voice is created

the user has entered Home B

Before this point, no archive exists.
Home A users should not see any messaging features.

### 15.3 Archive Home Screen (Continuity Hub Overview)

